        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 6:53PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 653 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Valhalla, or 10 miles south of Ryland, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Valhalla around 700 PM EDT.
Burgess and Snug Harbor around 725 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Goose Pond, Holiday
Island, Mavaton, Edenhouse, Saint Johns, Mount Gould, Hancock, Yeopim
Station, Forestburg, and Light Nixon Fork.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
northeastern North Carolina.</instruction>
